Paul Lawrie Wins Andalucia Open by 1 Shot for First Golf Title in 9 Years

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-03-27T16:32:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/paul-lawrie-wins-european-golf-s-andalucia-open-first-victory-in-9-years.html
Scotland ’s Paul Lawrie scored an
even-par 70 in his final round to win golf’s Andalucia Open
today and end a nine-year victory drought.  Lawrie, winner of the British Open in 1999, finished at 
12-under par in Malaga,  Spain . Johan Edfors of  Sweden  was
second at 11-under with  Chile ’s Felipe Aguilar a shot further 
back in third.  Lawrie picked up a check for 166,660 euros ($234,000) with
his sixth European Tour title.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  